  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Surender Kumar versus State of Himachal Pradesh pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_12_439_442','2025INSC1412'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SURENDER KUMAR<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF HIMACHAL PRADESH </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 12 S.C.R. 439</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1412</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006772025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : MANOJ MISRA, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether in the facts and circumstances of the case, the appellant could be convicted for an offence lesser than one punishable u/s.302, Penal Code, 1860. Headnotes&dagger; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; s.302; Exceptions to s.300 &ndash; Conviction u/s.302, when justified &ndash; be convicted for an offence lesser than one punishable u/s.302: Held: No &ndash; There are no mitigating circumstances on basis whereof the sentence may be reduced by altering the conviction of the appellant for an offence lesser than one punishable u/s.302, IPC &ndash; Deceased was inflicted<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 09-12-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 5398/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_12_439_442','2025INSC1412','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_12_439_442','